Business Brief -- Ames Department Stores Inc.:
   Deficit in First Six Months
   Of Fiscal 1993 Is Forecast
In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission,
Ames said it expects sales for the six-month period to range
from $1.08 billion to $1.17 billion, down 13% to 19% from
sales of $1.34 billion in the year-earlier six-month period.
   Ames, which is operating under protection of Chapter 11 of
the federal bankruptcy law, recently submitted a
reorganization plan. It has said that it expects to report
earnings of $2 million to $10 million for its recently
completed fourth quarter, before interest, Chapter 11
expenses, restructuring charges and income taxes.